  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "# Part 1: Artificial Neuron Anatomy\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1.1 Components of an Artificial Neuron\n",
    "\n",
    "An artificial neuron is the fundamental building block of neural networks.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Input Layer          Computation          Output\n",
    "    xвӮҒ в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҖwвӮҒв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n",
    "    xвӮӮ в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҖwвӮӮв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\n",
    "    xвӮғ в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҖwвӮғв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”ҖвҶ’ z = ОЈ(wбөўxбөў) + b в”Җв”ҖвҶ’ a = g(z) в”Җв”ҖвҶ’ output\n",
    "    ...             в”Ӯ\n",
    "    xвӮҷ в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҖwвӮҷв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n",
    "         +b (bias)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Mathematical Components:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Inputs (x)**: Feature vector x = [xвӮҒ, xвӮӮ, ..., xвӮҷ]\n",
    "2. **Weights (w)**: Learnable parameters w = [wвӮҒ, wвӮӮ, ..., wвӮҷ]\n",
    "3. **Bias (b)**: Learnable scalar that shifts activation\n",
    "4. **Pre-activation (z)**: z = wвӮҒxвӮҒ + wвӮӮxвӮӮ + ... + wвӮҷxвӮҷ + b\n",
    "5. **Activation function g(z)**: Introduces non-linearity\n",
    "6. **Output (a)**: a = g(z)\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's implement this step by step!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example: Single Neuron Computation\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Inputs (3 features)\n",
    "x = np.array([1.0, 2.0, 3.0])\n",
    "print(f\"Inputs (x): {x}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Weights\n",
    "w = np.array([0.5, -0.3, 0.8])\n",
    "print(f\"Weights (w): {w}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Bias\n",
    "b = 0.1\n",
    "print(f\"Bias (b): {b}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4. Pre-activation (z = wВ·x + b)\n",
    "z = np.dot(w, x) + b\n",
    "print(f\"\\nPre-activation (z): {z:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Calculation: ({w[0]}Г—{x[0]}) + ({w[1]}Г—{x[1]}) + ({w[2]}Г—{x[2]}) + {b} = {z:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 5. Activation function (sigmoid)\n",
    "def sigmoid(z):\n",
    "    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))\n",
    "\n",
    "a = sigmoid(z)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nActivation (a = Пғ(z)): {a:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nOutput: {a:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
