    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "# Part 2: Linear Algebra Representation\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2.1 Vector Notation: y = g(wбөҖx + b)\n",
    "\n",
    "The neuron computation can be elegantly expressed using linear algebra:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Scalar Form:**\n",
    "```\n",
    "z = wвӮҒxвӮҒ + wвӮӮxвӮӮ + ... + wвӮҷxвӮҷ + b\n",
    "y = g(z)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Vector Form:**\n",
    "```\n",
    "y = g(wбөҖx + b)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Where wбөҖx is the dot product (inner product) of vectors w and x."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate vector notation\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"VECTOR NOTATION DEMONSTRATION\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 1: Scalar form (manual)\n",
    "z_scalar = w[0]*x[0] + w[1]*x[1] + w[2]*x[2] + b\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMethod 1 - Scalar form:\")\n",
    "print(f\"z = {w[0]}Г—{x[0]} + {w[1]}Г—{x[1]} + {w[2]}Г—{x[2]} + {b}\")\n",
    "print(f\"z = {z_scalar:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 2: Dot product\n",
    "z_dot = np.dot(w, x) + b\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMethod 2 - Dot product:\")\n",
    "print(f\"z = wВ·x + b = np.dot(w, x) + b\")\n",
    "print(f\"z = {z_dot:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 3: Matrix multiplication (transpose)\n",
    "z_matmul = w.T @ x + b\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMethod 3 - Matrix multiplication:\")\n",
    "print(f\"z = wбөҖx + b = w.T @ x + b\")\n",
    "print(f\"z = {z_matmul:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify all methods give same result\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAll methods equal: {np.allclose(z_scalar, z_dot) and np.allclose(z_dot, z_matmul)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Final output\n",
    "y = sigmoid(z_dot)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFinal output: y = g(wбөҖx + b) = {y:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2.2 Matrix Notation for Multiple Neurons\n",
    "\n",
    "For a layer with m neurons and n inputs:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Z = WX + b\n",
    "A = g(Z)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "- W вҲҲ в„қбөҗЛЈвҒҝ: weight matrix\n",
    "- X вҲҲ в„қвҒҝЛЈбөҮ: input matrix (b = batch size)\n",
    "- b вҲҲ в„қбөҗ: bias vector\n",
    "- Z вҲҲ в„қбөҗЛЈбөҮ: pre-activation matrix\n",
    "- A вҲҲ в„қбөҗЛЈбөҮ: activation matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example: Layer with 4 neurons, 3 inputs, batch size 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Input matrix (3 features, 2 samples)\n",
    "X = np.array([\n",
    "    [1.0, 2.0],  # feature 1\n",
    "    [2.0, 3.0],  # feature 2\n",
    "    [3.0, 4.0]   # feature 3\n",
    "])\n",
    "print(f\"Input matrix X shape: {X.shape} (features Г— samples)\")\n",
    "print(f\"X =\\n{X}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Weight matrix (4 neurons, 3 inputs)\n",
    "W = np.random.randn(4, 3) * 0.5\n",
    "print(f\"Weight matrix W shape: {W.shape} (neurons Г— features)\")\n",
    "print(f\"W =\\n{W}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bias vector (4 neurons)\n",
    "b = np.random.randn(4, 1) * 0.1\n",
    "print(f\"Bias vector b shape: {b.shape} (neurons Г— 1)\")\n",
    "print(f\"b =\\n{b}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute pre-activation: Z = WX + b\n",
    "Z = W @ X + b\n",
    "print(f\"Pre-activation Z shape: {Z.shape} (neurons Г— samples)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Z = WX + b =\\n{Z}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply activation function\n",
    "A = sigmoid(Z)\n",
    "print(f\"Activation A shape: {A.shape} (neurons Г— samples)\")\n",
    "print(f\"A = Пғ(Z) =\\n{A}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"LAYER COMPUTATION SUMMARY\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(f\"Input:          X вҲҲ в„қВіЛЈВІ (3 features, 2 samples)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Weights:        W вҲҲ в„қвҒҙЛЈВі (4 neurons, 3 inputs each)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Bias:           b вҲҲ в„қвҒҙЛЈВ№ (4 neurons)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Pre-activation: Z = WX + b вҲҲ в„қвҒҙЛЈВІ\")\n",
    "print(f\"Activation:     A = Пғ(Z) вҲҲ в„қвҒҙЛЈВІ\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)"
   ]
  }
 ]
}
